## Summary

This final section reports key run-level metrics for reproducibility and quick quality check.
Use it as a compact snapshot of what was processed, how it was normalized, and how many probes were retained.

```{r summary_process_run}
read_if <- function(path) if (file.exists(path)) readr::read_csv(path, show_col_types = FALSE) else NULL
samples_res <- read_if("results/tables/samples_resolved.csv")
filt <- read_if("results/tables/filter_summary.csv")
summary_tbl <- tibble::tibble(
  metric = c("project_name", "array_type", "samples_loaded", "normalization_method", "probes_kept"),
  value = c(
    cfg$project$name,
    cfg$project$array_type,
    if (is.null(samples_res)) NA else nrow(samples_res),
    cfg$normalization$method,
    if (is.null(filt)) NA else filt$value[filt$metric == "probes_kept"][1]
  )
)
pretty_table(summary_tbl, caption = "Process run summary")
```
